1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Here's what science actually says about metastasis basics.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:08,400
Metastasis is how cancer spreads from one part of the body to another.

3
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,400
But how does that happen?

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,400
It starts when cancer cells break away from a tumor.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:17,600
They then enter the bloodstream or lymphatic system!

6
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:22,000
Once circulating, these cells can find new locations, creating secondary tumors.

7
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,600
This process is complex and still not fully understood.

8
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:29,200
Understanding metastasis is crucial for developing effective cancer treatments.

9
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:33,200
Scientists are making strides, but much remains to be discovered!

10
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:36,000
